Russia’s Spring-Grain Planting Reaches 28.2 Million Hectares

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-07T10:01:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/russia-s-spring-grain-planting-reaches-28-2-million-hectares-1-.html
Russian farmers sowed 28.2 million
hectares (69.7 million acres) with spring grains as of June 2,
the country’s Grain Union said today, citing Agriculture
Ministry data.  The country’s spring sowing was 9.4 percent higher than in
2010, the union said, and represented 93.3 percent of the
targeted area.  Spring wheat was sown on about 13.6 million hectares,
barley and sunflowers each exceeded 7 million hectares, corn was
on 1.6 million hectares, soya on 788,600 hectares, rape seeds on
611,600 hectares, and rice on 183,300 hectares, the  union  said
in an e-mailed statement.  The largest area, or 9.3 million hectares, was sown in the
Siberian federal district, followed by 8.4 million hectares in
the Volga area.  Spring sowing in  Russia ’s Central federal district was
complete on 3.4 million hectares, or 96 percent of the target
and in the Southern federal district it covered 2.2 million
hectares, or 89.5 percent of the plan, the union said. In the
Urals, 3.4 million hectares were sown and in the North-Caucasus
region 448,200 hectares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
